title: Lehigh Valley weekend highlight: Oktoberfest party at SteelStacks
text:
Oktoberfest at SteelStacks continues through Sunday with lots of German food, beer, music, games, contests and kids' activities.
Like music? On Sunday, Fritz's Polka Band kicks things off at noon, with other German music provided by Lancaster Liederkranz Hobby Chor and the International Alphorn Ensemble. Popular State College cover band My Hero Zero brings things to a raucous close 4-8 p.m.
Sunday also features the 5th Annual Dachshund Races at 3 p.m., as well as Barrel Rolling, Stein Races and the Masskrugstemmen competition.
Vote for your favorite scarecrow or make your own glass pumpkin with ArtsQuest's Glass Studio artists.
Admission is free. Info: steelstacks.org .
